modules.description: Calculates 64-bit and 128-bit hash values for strings and byte sequences using the FarmHash algorithm. It supports direct hashing of input data and provides a way to combine hash values incrementally. This is useful for applications requiring fast, low-collision hashing such as data indexing or checksum validation.

Computes numeric hash values of strings using various bit depths and seed configurations, including 32-bit, 64-bit, and 128-bit outputs. Supports seeded hashing for deterministic results and fingerprinting for compact string identification. Handles input strings to generate hash tuples for high-precision unique identifiers.
